<font color="#FF0000">CHEAP SHOTS FROM THE DARK.</font><br>
<tt>Mon Aug 11 23:55:19 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I recall the importance of interrogating freshly captured enemy soldiers.  I remember their fear and vulnerability as they were whisked to the rear... some wounded, all with their hands bound behind their back.  They were no longer threats...fierce and deadly opponents... unarmed and beaten, to me they became pitiful humans.<br>
I too, remember the combat soldiers who delivered these POW's to me for extraction.  They were men of honor who had just recently engaged these vanquished fighters.<br>
In the rear, it was a different story... REMF's and ARVN's, who didn't have the guts to engaged these Cong in the bush, took some sort of sick pleasure of kicking these POW's in the groin and punching them in the face.  Not to vent their anger... or to interrogate... just to satisfy some sick need to mask their lack of masculinity.  I called it &quot;Cheap Shots,&quot; then... and I call it cheap shots now.<br>
I'm sorry if I have been guilty of it at the keyboard... I hope that some of you will think about it.<br><br>
Enough Said,<br><br>
MUSTANG TWO FOUR
